{"id":"rcl-nzv","title":"Remove axios: migrate react-v18 Storybook tests to @storybook/addon-vitest","description":"Replace @storybook/test-runner + start-server-and-test (both pull wait-on -> axios) with @storybook/addon-vitest browser-mode tests. Eliminates all axios from the tree (vulnerable 0.27.2 + safe 1.17.0). Stack ready: SB10.4.4, vitest4.1.8, playwright1.55.1. Was previously deferred as unstable under pnpm.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-06-15T23:20:10.996090Z","created_by":"claude","updated_at":"2026-06-15T23:31:56.617295Z","closed_at":"2026-06-15T23:31:56.617225Z","close_reason":"Migrated react-v18 to @storybook/addon-vitest (unified vitest.config.ts projects + --project flag). All axios/joi/uuid removed from tree; pnpm qa green (27 unit + 30 story tests). Dropped dead osv-scanner overrides.","source_repo":"react-component-library","source_repo_path":"/Users/neural/Code/node/react-component-library","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
{"id":"rcl-q64","title":"Cross-framework component swap + Tauri integration demo","description":"End-goal: a Tauri app (Rust backend) imports components through a single type-safe adapter that re-exports the component contract. Swapping the component library (React <-> Svelte) is a one-import change; a non-conforming library fails type-check. Design is decoupled from the app: themes (light/dark + arbitrary), easy color/component swap, rem-based sizing.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-06-15T19:32:26.390462Z","created_by":"claude","updated_at":"2026-06-15T19:32:26.390462Z","source_repo":"react-component-library","source_repo_path":"/Users/neural/Code/node/react-component-library","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
{"id":"rcl-q64.1","title":"Type-safe contract adapter module","description":"Per-implementation adapter entrypoints only. Each concrete library exports its own contract-checked adapter, e.g. reactV18ContractAdapter. Application code can swap implementations by changing a single import line from one implementation package to another; no separate higher-level app-facing adapter package is required.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-06-15T19:32:26.441989Z","created_by":"claude","updated_at":"2026-06-16T00:10:54.878879Z","closed_at":"2026-06-16T00:10:54.878832Z","close_reason":"Implemented per-implementation contract adapter pattern for React v18 and recorded architecture decision: no separate higher-level app-facing adapter package; swapping is a one-line import change between implementation packages.","source_repo":"react-component-library","source_repo_path":"/Users/neural/Code/node/react-component-library","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rcl-q64.1","depends_on_id":"rcl-q64","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-06-15T19:32:26.441989Z","created_by":"claude","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
